The governor of Kaduna state, Malam Nasir El-Rufai, will tomorrow (Wednesday) flag-off his campaign for re-election in 2019. The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Kaduna state had on December 2, released the list of members of its campaign council and directorates and named Mr. Ben Kure as the Director-General. The Campaign Council which was inaugurated on the 4th of December 2018, is chaired by Malam Nasir El-Rufai, the party’s candidate for the governorship election, with his running mate, Dr.Hadiza Sabuwa Balarabe, as deputy chairman. A statement from the campaign council secretary, Muhammed B. Shuaib, said the party’s three senatorial candidates, Barnabas Yusuf Bala, Uba Sani and Suleiman Abdu Kwari are the campaign vice-chairmen. The flag-off is expected to galvanise political activities in the state. 2019 election is between thieves and honest people – El-Rufai 2019 elections between thieves and honest people - El-Rufai Kaduna APC appoints 1342 into  campaign council for El-Rufai’s re-election